    • getResourceId

      protected final String getResourceId()
      The resource ID is always required but does not necessarily need to be provided by the user. In case the user didn't provide one, a random UUID is generated automatically.
      Returns:
      Resource ID provided by user or a randomly generated one if no ID was provided

    • self

      protected final B self()
      This method is required to allow common methods to return the concrete builder and enable all builders to have this method
      Returns:
      the self-builder

    • checkRequired

      protected final <T> void checkRequired(T obj, String errorMsg)
      This method works similar to Objects.requireNonNull, but instead of throwing a NullPointerException, this one will throw BuilderException with a message supplied by the errorMsgSupplier
      Type Parameters:
      T - is the generic type of obj
      Parameters:
      obj - is the object which will be checked for Null
      errorMsg - will be shown in the BuilderException in case of an Error
